x3270 Version 3.0.2

x3270 is an IBM 3278 terminal emulator for X windows.

Documentation is in the Docs directory.  The files are:

    Intro	What x3270 is

    Lineage	Where x3270 came from (copyright stuff)

    Build	How to build and install x3270

    FAQ		Frequently Asked Questions (what to do when something goes
		 wrong)

    Attributes	A translation table for 3270 field attributes

    Resources	Voluminous documentation of all the X resources used by
		x3270

    Charset	An explanation of x3270's use of fonts and character sets

    New.*	What's new in this release

    Bugs	What's borken in this release

    Wishlist	What isn't in this release

Please read "Build" before going ahead and building the program.  Also, if you
have a problem, scan through "FAQ"; there are lots of interesting answers
there.

Updates to x3270 are avaliable on ftp.x.org (export.lcs.mit.edu).  Fixes are
distributed as patch files (you will need gnu patch to apply them) under the
name fix.nn, e.g., the first fix to version 3.0.2 will be x3270-3.0.2.fix01.

Feel free to send comments, criticism, suggestions, complaints, etc., to Paul
Mattes (x3270@cnt.com).  Problems will be addressed as time and resources
permit.
